Pre-Game Insights: Faroe Islands aim to put an end to their three-game losing run in all competitions and they are likely to fight tooth and nail against the Macedonians.
A man to watch in the home team will be Klaemint Olsen, who has netted 10 goals in 63 appearances for the national team.
North Macedonia are on a three-game losing run as well.
North Macedonia are likely to adopt an attack-minded approach in Saturday’s showdown.
The likes of Alioski, Churlinov, Bardhi, and Elmas are the most notable players in the visiting team.
North Macedonia defeated Faroe Islands 1-0 when the two sides met in a friendly last year.
